contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:45.200 --> 00:47.100
Opening.

00:49.600 --> 00:51.500
- Thanks.
- Bobby Simone.

00:51.500 --> 00:54.400
How's it going, Ray?

00:54.300 --> 00:57.900
How do you think? I'm in
the system here, Bobby.

00:57.900 --> 01:01.100
Yeah, they brought you down
for your appeal hearing, huh?

01:01.100 --> 01:03.400
My appeal.

01:03.300 --> 01:05.400
- Hey, you never know, right?
- That's right.

01:05.400 --> 01:07.300
'Cause you heard
about the trial, right?

01:07.300 --> 01:09.800
That little genius from Legal Aid
gets me three to five.

01:09.800 --> 01:12.300
I'm just the lookout.
Meanwhile, the principals...

01:12.300 --> 01:14.700
they mention a few names,
they're on the street already.

01:14.700 --> 01:17.000
I'm just talking
about justice here, Bobby.

01:17.000 --> 01:20.000
And I asked you to help me out at the time.
You turned your back.

01:20.000 --> 01:23.600
Is this why you asked me to come down here,
so that we can go over all of this again?

01:26.700 --> 01:29.100
I'm sorry. L...

01:29.100 --> 01:31.600
I just...

01:31.600 --> 01:33.500
I don't think
so good, you know?

01:33.500 --> 01:36.000
I'm upset all the time, Bobby.

01:39.500 --> 01:42.300
- I need your help, Bobby.
- There's no way I can help you, Ray.

01:42.200 --> 01:44.800
Don't worry.

01:44.700 --> 01:48.100
I'm bringing something
to the table- information.

01:49.100 --> 01:51.800
This guy I've been hanging
with in the yard...

01:51.700 --> 01:54.700
he worked this job some three years ago-
an armored car heist.

01:54.700 --> 01:58.400
A couple ex-cops were driving.
They both got killed.

01:58.300 --> 02:01.100
- You talking about the Grandpa Car?
- I heard him mention that.

02:01.000 --> 02:04.300
That's what they called it.
Now, according to him, they got away clean.

02:04.200 --> 02:07.600
Him and three other guys.
Is this ringing any bells?

02:07.500 --> 02:11.000
The Grandpa Car's a real case, Ray.
You got any names?

02:11.000 --> 02:14.700
I got a first and last on one of the guys
and a street name on one of the others.

02:14.700 --> 02:17.200
Do you think that's worth
something to the D. A?

02:17.200 --> 02:19.700
I'll see what I can find out.

02:19.600 --> 02:23.300
You know, I don't blame you
for what's happened to me, Bobby...

02:23.200 --> 02:27.400
but I got to get out of here.

02:27.400 --> 02:31.200
I gotta go, Ray.
That's from my job.

02:31.100 --> 02:34.200
Now, you tell the D.A.
I got those names.

02:34.200 --> 02:36.500
- I will. On the gate.
- Opening.

02:36.500 --> 02:39.100
- I'll let you know.
- Yeah, sure.

02:39.100 --> 02:41.700
Go ahead.
Walk out of here.

04:08.600 --> 04:10.400
- Hey.
- Hey, what's going on?

04:10.500 --> 04:12.100
Yeah, two people shot.
One D.O.A.

04:12.100 --> 04:14.900
Perp fled on foot. Got a couple
of witnesses over there.

04:14.900 --> 04:17.800
- Yeah, what's their story?
- Some guy showed up, started shooting.

04:17.700 --> 04:20.300
Guy shot in the shoulder's
just a flesh wound.

04:20.300 --> 04:22.700
- Wanna talk to him before they take him?
- Yeah, what's his name?

04:22.700 --> 04:25.000
- Samuel Velasquez.
- Samwell"?

04:25.900 --> 04:28.500
Samuel?
I'm Detective Sipowicz.

04:28.500 --> 04:31.800
This is Detective Simone. What can you
tell us about the guy that shot you?

04:31.800 --> 04:34.900
Oh, it was crazy, man.
Th-This black dude...

04:34.800 --> 04:38.200
he comes into the store, right,
and he starts screaming all this racial trash.

04:38.100 --> 04:40.600
- Then all of a sudden, I'm shot.
- You were the first one shot?

04:40.600 --> 04:42.500
No. He shot Luis first,
and then he started...

04:42.500 --> 04:44.400
waving the gun around,
shooting everybody.

04:44.400 --> 04:46.600
- He shot you first, man.
- Man, it was crazy.

04:46.600 --> 04:49.000
- It was all happening at the same time.
- All you guys were in there?

04:48.900 --> 04:51.500
Yeah, man. He was drunk. That's how come
he didn't just killed everybody.

04:51.500 --> 04:53.600
- He was a big guy.
- No, he wasn't that big.

04:53.600 --> 04:56.200
He was medium. He was black.
Real, real, real black.

04:56.200 --> 04:58.300
- He was about 50, man.
- You never seen this guy before?

04:58.400 --> 05:01.100
Yeah, I've seen him like maybe
coming out of the subway or something.

05:01.100 --> 05:03.300
- So maybe he lives around here?
- Yeah, maybe.

05:03.300 --> 05:05.300
We're not going to find out
this is about dope, right?

05:05.300 --> 05:08.900
You think 'cause we're boricua that means
we deal dope? What's wrong with you, man?

05:08.700 --> 05:10.600
- What's wrong with you? I got shot over here.
- All right.

05:10.700 --> 05:13.900
Take it easy, huh?
James, what do you got?

05:13.800 --> 05:16.600
We gave the place a quick toss.
We didn't come up with anything.

05:16.600 --> 05:18.500
- These guys are half loaded.
- Yeah.

05:18.600 --> 05:21.200
- You want us to start the canvass?
- Yeah. Keep your eyes open.

05:21.200 --> 05:24.200
Happens that the mariachi troupe
over here is telling the truth...

05:24.100 --> 05:26.200
we got a nut out there
with a gun.

05:26.300 --> 05:29.300
- You guys, we're gonna have to go over to the station house.
- James, take my car.

05:29.200 --> 05:32.100
- Sure.
- But this better not take all day, you know what I'm saying?

05:32.100 --> 05:34.600
Hey, your friend Luis
here just got shot.

05:34.600 --> 05:36.700
You gonna tell me about
Luis, man? I know the guy, man.

05:36.600 --> 05:38.800
- We don't feel up to this, man, okay?
- You're in mourning.

05:38.900 --> 05:40.800
All right.
I understand.

05:42.700 --> 05:45.200
- Get in here.
- Ayayay.

05:53.400 --> 05:56.100
Hey, man.
I can't believe this.

05:56.100 --> 05:58.100
Just keep looking.

05:59.100 --> 06:03.100
Excuse me. L- I was told downstairs
this is where to make my complaint.

06:03.100 --> 06:05.100
Oh. Um, uh...

06:05.000 --> 06:07.100
Detective Medavoy can see you.
Detective, you're up.

06:07.100 --> 06:10.300
- Oh. Can I help you?
- Yes. I'm the victim of an assault.

06:10.300 --> 06:15.400
Well, right this way. Let's get
some information about what happened.

06:15.200 --> 06:18.200
My name's, uh-
My name's Peter Cahill.

06:18.200 --> 06:21.200
- Have a seat, Mr. Cahill.
- Thank you.

06:21.100 --> 06:23.400
Uh, how badly were you
hurt in this incident?

06:23.400 --> 06:26.100
Uh, bruises
up and down my arms...

06:26.100 --> 06:28.600
and, uh, feel this bump.

06:28.600 --> 06:30.600
It's quite large.

06:30.600 --> 06:35.300
It looks painful. Were you struck
with a foreign object?

06:35.200 --> 06:37.100
With a blunt-edged sword.

06:37.100 --> 06:39.900
D- Do you know
the person who hit you?

06:39.900 --> 06:42.500
The stage actor, Raleigh Gibson.
You probably know him.

06:42.500 --> 06:45.000
Uh, no, I don't get to
the theater too much.

06:45.000 --> 06:46.900
Well, in the middle
of the sword fight last night...

06:46.900 --> 06:50.400
he completely abandoned
the choreography and attacked me.

06:50.300 --> 06:53.100
I take it
you're an actor as well.

06:53.000 --> 06:56.100
Yeah. Last week,
he nearly put my eye out.

06:56.000 --> 06:58.700
Did you speak to anyone
at the theater about this?

06:58.700 --> 07:01.900
They don't want to deal with it.
They tell themselves he's box office.

07:01.800 --> 07:05.000
They should tell the empty seats.
Meanwhile, I take a nightly beating.

07:07.200 --> 07:11.100
Procedure, Mr. Cahill- I look into
your complaint, talk to the relevant parties...

07:11.000 --> 07:13.000
and then there will be
a decision on charges.

07:13.000 --> 07:15.300
I work at
the Ludlow Theater.

07:15.200 --> 07:19.500
Ask Roland Edmunds about him.
Ask Donna Stein.

07:19.300 --> 07:22.800
Definitely. I'll check
the matter out.

07:22.700 --> 07:24.700
Well, uh, thank you
for coming in.

07:24.700 --> 07:27.800
Well, I was- I was
on my way to the doctor.

07:36.400 --> 07:39.800
- May I help you?
- Yes, I'd like to speak to the detective in charge.

07:39.700 --> 07:42.000
Arthur Fancy. I'm lieutenant
in charge of the squad.

07:42.000 --> 07:45.400
- Louis Folsom. I'm pastor at Bethel A.M.E.
- How do you do?

07:45.300 --> 07:48.200
Why don't you come in?
Have a seat.

07:53.800 --> 07:55.500
Lieutenant...

07:55.500 --> 07:58.100
one of my parishioners was involved
in a shooting this morning.

07:58.100 --> 07:59.700
He says he shot two men.

07:59.800 --> 08:03.200
There was a multiple shooting
at a bodega on Third Street.

08:03.100 --> 08:06.800
- Sounds like the incident.
- So what's the man's name?

08:06.800 --> 08:10.600
He says when he fired the gun,
he was in fear for his life.

08:10.500 --> 08:13.500
Well, if he was in danger,
that's a very important factor.

08:13.500 --> 08:15.200
So, where can
we find him?

08:15.100 --> 08:19.200
I'd like to be able to tell him I spoke
with the man that he would be talking to.

08:23.000 --> 08:26.700
You can tell him that.
So how can we find him, Pastor?

08:27.800 --> 08:29.800
His name is Gregory Leight.

08:29.900 --> 08:32.700
He's not far from here.
I'll go get him.

08:32.600 --> 08:34.200
Okay.

08:47.600 --> 08:49.900
Your bodega
witnesses set up?

08:49.900 --> 08:52.100
They want to know do they get paid
if they pick out the shooter.

08:52.100 --> 08:54.900
It's part of dealing
with their grief.

08:54.900 --> 08:57.700
A suspect's coming in with his minister.
We'll get his statement...

08:57.700 --> 08:59.600
have the witnesses take a look.

08:59.600 --> 09:02.400
Hey, Lieu. We turned up a neighbor on the canvass.
She saw a kid running down the street...

09:02.300 --> 09:04.300
screaming just before
the shots were fired.

09:04.200 --> 09:06.200
Didn't know the kid,
but she saw him come out.

09:06.200 --> 09:08.200
Somebody's gonna have to keep
these guys in the mug books.

09:08.200 --> 09:11.900
- Lieu says the shooter's
coming. - Is that right? - Yeah.

09:11.900 --> 09:15.300
As soon as you look at the guy, James,
get some fillers from the shelters for a lineup.

09:15.300 --> 09:18.800
And, Adrianne, run a Gregory Leight
through B.C.I. I'm not sure of the spelling.

09:18.700 --> 09:21.300
- Okay.
- Did the minister say how it happened?

09:21.300 --> 09:24.300
- No, but he said the guy'd give a full statement.
- Can't hate a ground ball.

09:24.300 --> 09:26.600
Okay, I'll be there in the interview.
He asked for that.

09:26.600 --> 09:28.600
Yeah, all right.

09:28.600 --> 09:31.200
Lieu. Uh, that guy
Ray DiSalvo...

09:31.200 --> 09:33.800
The guy I grew up with, took a collar
last year for moving coke.

09:33.700 --> 09:36.300
Yeah, worked at
that rumba joint.

09:36.300 --> 09:38.800
He's on the inside now.
Claims a guy on his tier copped to...

09:38.800 --> 09:41.300
sticking up the Grandpa Car
with three other skells.

09:41.300 --> 09:44.100
- Did he give any names?
- He says he's got a full name on one of the guys...

09:44.100 --> 09:46.800
- and another guy's nickname.
- That was Roberts's case.

09:46.800 --> 09:48.500
- The Grandpa Car?
- Yeah. Yeah.

09:48.500 --> 09:50.800
- Well, see if the D.A. Wants to deal.
- I'll call Sylvia.

09:52.800 --> 09:55.700
Lieu...

09:59.100 --> 10:00.800
This is Gregory Leight.

10:03.000 --> 10:06.400
Uh, he's got the gun.

10:06.300 --> 10:09.400
I'm Arthur Fancy. I'll take your statement
with Detective Sipowicz.

10:09.400 --> 10:11.800
I'm trying to reach A.D.A. Costas.

10:11.800 --> 10:15.700
- Okay.
- I'll tell your wife that I saw you go in with the lieutenant.

10:17.700 --> 10:19.700
This way.

10:24.500 --> 10:26.400
Have a seat, Mr. Leight.

10:26.400 --> 10:30.800
- Miles, put this in evidence lockup.
- Okay, Lieu.

10:37.300 --> 10:42.800
So, uh, your pastor said you wanted
to talk to us about a shooting.

10:42.600 --> 10:45.700
Those drunks down at
the bodega went after my son.

10:45.600 --> 10:47.700
Tell us what happened.

10:47.700 --> 10:50.500
Well, I sent him out for bread,
and after about 10 minutes...

10:50.500 --> 10:52.400
I hear
all this yelling.

10:52.400 --> 10:55.900
His friend comes to my door,
crying and carrying on...

10:55.900 --> 10:57.900
and saying that
Junior's in trouble.

10:57.800 --> 11:00.000
- So what was his friend's name?
- Delroy.

11:00.000 --> 11:02.300
My wife would know
his last name.

11:02.300 --> 11:05.500
But he was yelling that they were
beating Gregory down at the bodega.

11:05.500 --> 11:07.900
He said, Mr. Leight,
they're beating Junior!"

11:07.900 --> 11:11.000
So I grabbed an old gun
I keep in the house.

11:10.900 --> 11:13.700
And I went out in the street,
and here comes my son running...

11:13.600 --> 11:16.000
his face all
covered with blood.

11:16.000 --> 11:21.200
- So how old is your son?
- Ten. Ten years old.

11:21.100 --> 11:23.300
There's drunks
in that place.

11:23.300 --> 11:27.800
I told him he's never supposed to
go near that filthy place!

11:27.600 --> 11:31.400
Just to save a half a block to the grocery.
Now look at all this trouble.

11:31.300 --> 11:34.600
So when you saw your son,
was he alone in the street?

11:34.500 --> 11:36.400
Was anyone chasing him?

11:36.400 --> 11:40.200
No, there was just somebody looking out from
the bodega, but nobody was chasing him.

11:40.100 --> 11:43.400
- And you went on to the bodega?
- I sent him home.

11:43.400 --> 11:47.200
- Then I went in.
- Did you have your gun out?

11:47.000 --> 11:50.500
Not then. I said...

11:50.400 --> 11:54.000
Hey. Who beat my boy?"

11:54.000 --> 11:57.100
And there was a lot of yelling,
screaming back and forth.

11:57.000 --> 12:02.000
And some racial stuff. And one of them
said to the other some Spanish.

12:01.900 --> 12:04.900
And the guy behind the counter,
he grabbed beneath.

12:04.900 --> 12:08.500
And then the guy in the aisle
started coming at me.

12:08.400 --> 12:11.300
And that's when
I pulled out my gun.

12:11.200 --> 12:14.400
'Cause the guy behind
the counter was going for a gun...

12:14.300 --> 12:16.900
and the guy in the aisle
was coming at me.

12:18.400 --> 12:21.900
I was so upset
about my boy.

12:21.800 --> 12:23.800
And you shot 'em both.

12:31.300 --> 12:34.300
I have been a longshoreman
for 25 years.

12:34.300 --> 12:37.500
I've never even had
a parking ticket.

12:41.700 --> 12:43.700
What do you want to do?

12:43.600 --> 12:46.600
Talk to the son and the friend
who came and got him.

12:46.600 --> 12:49.800
Even if they back the father's story,
he's looking at manslaughter.

12:49.700 --> 12:52.600
- That's where I want you to start, Andy.
- No problem.

12:52.600 --> 12:54.800
Want me to run the witnesses
through B.C. I?

12:54.700 --> 12:57.900
- They don't look like no choir boys.
- Yeah.

12:57.900 --> 13:00.400
Whoever's in with him,
I'll, uh...

13:00.400 --> 13:02.900
I'll make sure they don't
let him write nothing.

13:02.900 --> 13:05.100
Yeah. Okay. Thanks.

13:05.100 --> 13:07.000
Hey, no problem.

13:26.900 --> 13:28.800
How'd the hearing go?

13:28.800 --> 13:31.900
It was a joke, Bobby. Judge didn't
give us five minutes.

13:31.900 --> 13:35.400
Ray, this is Assistant D.A.
Sylvia Costas.

13:35.300 --> 13:37.200
- Ray DiSalvo.
- How do you do?

13:37.300 --> 13:40.400
Miss Costas wants to talk to you
about this armored car job.

13:40.300 --> 13:42.400
No problem.
I'm all for women's lib.

13:42.300 --> 13:46.600
You got the D.A. Sent me away
beat a mile.

13:46.600 --> 13:48.200
Jewish guy,
big pot belly.

13:48.200 --> 13:50.400
Maury Abrams.
I've been looking over your file.

13:50.400 --> 13:52.300
I meant no disrespect.

13:52.400 --> 13:55.400
He was doing his job.

13:55.300 --> 13:58.600
Mr. DiSalvo, if the information
that you've offered...

13:58.600 --> 14:00.300
on the Grandpa Car
produced arrests...

14:00.300 --> 14:03.200
we'd support reducing
your sentence by half.

14:03.100 --> 14:05.500
Support?
Uh-uh.

14:05.500 --> 14:07.300
I'm not giving up names
on support.

14:07.300 --> 14:09.300
She's gotta put it
that way, Ray.

14:09.200 --> 14:12.400
What happens if you guys blow the arrest?
That's not my fault if you guys screw this up.

14:12.400 --> 14:15.200
- We won't screw it up.
- How do I know that, Bobby?

14:20.300 --> 14:23.800
- Reduced by half?
- With the time served, that's only four more months.

14:23.800 --> 14:28.200
- Yeah, but I didn't do nothing. I was just the lookout.
- Ray, Ray, Ray.

14:28.000 --> 14:29.800
Do you want to
go through with this?

14:30.900 --> 14:34.500
- Do I have a choice?
- Come on.

14:36.600 --> 14:38.500
Sorry.

14:42.300 --> 14:47.100
The guy I'm in with,
his name is Jimmy Fredo.

14:48.400 --> 14:50.800
The guys he said
he did thejob with...

14:50.700 --> 14:52.900
one is Tommy Rotella-
is the full name I got.

14:52.900 --> 14:55.800
And the second guy's
nickname is called Bic.

14:55.800 --> 14:58.800
- First or last name on the nickname?
- I don't know.

14:58.800 --> 15:03.100
All right, this Jimmy Fredo's the guy
that you're in jail with right now.

15:02.900 --> 15:05.900
He gave you Tom Rotella and another guy
whose nickname is Bic.

15:05.900 --> 15:08.200
- Right.
- You said there were three guys on the outside.

15:09.700 --> 15:11.700
That's all I got.
They got away clean.

15:11.700 --> 15:15.100
They're living good. Jimmy's doing time.
I don't know the score.

15:17.800 --> 15:20.600
All right, Mr. DiSalvo.

15:21.900 --> 15:24.300
All right, Ray,
we're gonna look into this.

15:24.200 --> 15:27.400
What, you're going to send me
back upstate now? I gotta go back there?

15:27.400 --> 15:30.100
They'll keep you down here
till we see if this all works out.

15:30.000 --> 15:33.000
You'll be in
administrative segregation.

15:37.000 --> 15:39.300
But it's still jail, right?

15:47.300 --> 15:49.300
Gregory.

15:50.300 --> 15:52.200
Gregory.

15:52.200 --> 15:55.100
The police are here.
They have to ask you some questions.

15:56.200 --> 15:58.700
I'm Detective Sipowicz,
Gregory.

15:58.700 --> 16:01.000
How did you
get those bruises?

16:01.000 --> 16:03.400
- Those guys hit me.
- Tell me the guys you mean.

16:03.400 --> 16:06.700
- In the bodega.
- How come they did that?

16:06.600 --> 16:10.200
- I don't know.
- He knows he wasn't supposed to be down there.

16:10.200 --> 16:12.200
He was supposed to
go to the Korean place.

16:12.200 --> 16:14.600
Him and his friend didn't
want to walk the extra block.

16:14.600 --> 16:16.700
You need to let us ask the questions,
Mrs. Leight.

16:18.400 --> 16:21.000
We're trying to find out
what happened with your dad.

16:20.900 --> 16:23.800
So we really need you
to think about this.

16:23.800 --> 16:26.900
I don't know. They said
it was the change.

16:26.900 --> 16:29.800
- The change?
- It was for a loaf of bread.

16:29.800 --> 16:32.900
I had the exact change,
so I put it on the counter.

16:32.900 --> 16:35.500
- He didn't like it there.
- Who didn't?

16:35.400 --> 16:40.000
The guy behind the counter. He pushed it
back at me, said put it in his hand.

16:39.900 --> 16:42.600
Then 20 of the cents
went on the floor.

16:42.600 --> 16:44.900
Then the other guy come up
behind me and told me to pick it up.

16:44.900 --> 16:48.500
And I said, 'The counter guy pushed it
on the floor. He should pick it up."

16:48.500 --> 16:50.800
Then they started
beating on me...

